lid; background-color: #ccc;">  rounded up quotes from customers whose mone=
y is gone</a>, and the customers are all like =E2=80=9Cwell yes obviously=
=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Others are trying to accept their losses and m=
ove on, despite the lost money. That=E2=80=99s the case for William Casey.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At first, he ignored the warning signs in the =
digital asset space.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWhen you follow crypto for long enoug=
h, you get calloused to the threat of loss,=E2=80=9D the Texas-based trader=
 said. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It doesn=E2=80=99t quite feel real for him yet=
, and he=E2=80=99s taking a =E2=80=9Cwait-and-see approach.=E2=80=9D He sai=
d he=E2=80=99s been investing in crypto since 2013 and has made more than $=
400,000 over the years.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThis life-changing amount of money wa=
s so easy come, easy go that I can=E2=80=99t help but feel disassociated fr=
om it,=E2=80=9D Casey said. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m just kind of letting thing=
s happen =E2=80=94 it would be nice if we got our money back, but right now=
 it=E2=80=99s just a kind of quiet resignation.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He was putting regular deposits into BlockFi=
=E2=80=99s interest-bearing accounts to sit and appreciate, enticed by yiel=
ds as high as 9.75%. Although he knew keeping his savings in crypto was a =
=E2=80=9Cgamble,=E2=80=9D he believed BlockFi was safer than other platform=
s since it was based in the US.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIf Bitcoin just dropped to zero, that=
 would be one thing,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CBut now it feels like some =
kid just stole my money and it doesn=E2=80=99t sit well with me.=E2=80=9D</=
p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CBlockFi Bankruptcy Hijacks More Custo=
mer Cash,=E2=80=9D is the headline. Here we go again.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously this is an=C2=A0<em>imperfect=C2=A0<=
/em>system, both in the sense that somewhere out there there probably are=
=C2=A0less sophisticated investors who genuinely thought that the accounts =
paying 9.75% interest on cryptocurrency were safe, and in the sense that lo=
ts of crypto platforms =E2=80=94=C2=A0including both FTX and BlockFi =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0tried to give off an air of legitimacy and trustworthiness that mi=
ght have led people to think =E2=80=9Cthis time is different,=C2=A0<em>thes=
e=C2=A0</em>platforms won=E2=80=99t lose my money.=E2=80=9D The damage here=
 is not=C2=A0<em>zero</em>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But it is=C2=A0<em>hard</em>, particularly in =
the US, to find people who (1) know enough about crypto to be able to buy i=
t but (2) know so little about crypto that they are surprised when a crypto=
=C2=A0exchange loses their money. Crypto does a pretty good job =E2=80=94=
=C2=A0not on purpose or anything, but nevertheless =E2=80=94=C2=A0of educat=
ing its investors about how they will lose their money. And then when it ha=
ppens, they shrug and say =E2=80=9Ceasy come, easy go.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
